cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision for autonomous driving, specifically on moving object detection using fisheye surround-view cameras. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for the autonomous vehicle to estimate collision risk and calculate an optimal trajectory, which falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The proposed CNN architecture and lightweight encoder design also suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the need for improved security measures in autonomous driving, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
